Vice President Kamala Harris announced the launch of the United States-Caribbean Partnership to Address the Climate Crisis (PACC 2030). This partnership aims to support energy infrastructure and climate resilience projects in the Caribbean region. The four main aspects of the partnership include identifying new clean energy projects, providing technical assistance to make them viable, showcasing the projects to investors, and improving access to development financing. The involvement of the private sector is seen as crucial to the success of this initiative. Harris emphasized that addressing the climate crisis is a top priority for the United States, and collaboration with Caribbean nations is essential. The Vice President also expressed the importance of strengthening the U.S.-Caribbean relationship and addressing other important issues together.